defs.docs: Per-object thread-local storage

defs.name: ThreadLocal
defs.docs: Thread-local variable wrapper

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new empty `ThreadLocal`.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns the element for the current thread, if it exists.

defs.name: get_or
defs.docs:
Returns the element for the current thread, or creates it if it doesn't
 exist.

defs.name: get_or_try
defs.value: fn <F, E> (&self, create: F) -> Result<&T, E>
defs.docs:
Returns the element for the current thread, or creates it if it doesn't
 exist. If `create` fails, that error is returned and no element is
 added.

defs.name: iter_mut
defs.docs: Returns a mutable iterator over the local values of all threads.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs:
Removes all thread-specific values from the `ThreadLocal`, effectively
 reseting it to its original state.

defs.name: get_default
defs.docs:
Returns the element for the current thread, or creates a default one if
 it doesn't exist.

defs.name: IterMut
defs.docs: Mutable iterator over the contents of a `ThreadLocal`.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: An iterator that moves out of a `ThreadLocal`.
